@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Obliks" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Obliks runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a tile that contains a mirror (indicated
by a diagonal bar), that mirror will toggle from one state to the
other. When mirrors are correctly aligned from the two entries to
exits, both rays will be generated and you will get points
according to the number of mirrors, and whether or not the number
of mirrors used by each ray match...

  Scoring goes like this: When both rays use the same number of
mirrors, both number of mirrors are added to the score. Otherwise,
the number of points will be the total number of mirrors used by
both mirrors, divided by the difference in the number of
mirrors...

  For example: if ray number 1 uses 15 mirrors and ray number 2
uses 11 mirrors, the number of points you get will be:

  (15+11)/(15-11) = 26/4 = 6.5

...which will be rounded to 6 points. So suffice it to say, try as
much as possible to have the same number of mirrors for both rays
to score the maximum number of points!

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

